# Optional Binding (if let)

A much safer way to unwrap is using `if let`.

```swift
var secretCode: String? = "1234"

if let safeCode = secretCode {
    print("The code is \(safeCode)")
} else {
    print("There was no code inside the box.")
}
```
This safely peeks inside `secretCode`. If there is data, it pours it into a brand new, non-optional variable called `safeCode`.

